## 1. Data Collection by Ceibo Apps
Applications and extensions published by Ceibo Apps are designed with a **privacy-first** approach. Our products:

* **Do not** require user accounts.
* **Do not** include advertising.
* **Do not** use analytics or tracking technologies.
* **Do not** communicate with external servers operated by Ceibo Apps.

All core functionality operates **locally** on your device. We do not collect, store, transmit, or share personal or sensitive user data.

## 2. Device Permissions
If an app or extension requests device permissions (such as camera, microphone, storage, audio, or browser access), these permissions are used **solely** to provide the product's core functionality.

No data accessed through these permissions is collected, stored, or transmitted by Ceibo Apps. We do not share any data with third parties.

## 3. Chrome Extensions

### Minimal Save Image

**Images never leave your browser.** When you right-click an image and choose a format, the extension re-downloads that image from the page you are already on, decodes it with Chrome's built-in canvas, re-encodes it in the format you picked, and hands the result to Chrome's download manager. All of this happens inside your browser.

**What is stored locally:**

| Data | Where | Why |
|------|-------|-----|
| Your settings (format, quality, subfolder) | `chrome.storage.local` | So the extension remembers your preferences |
| A count of images converted | `chrome.storage.local` | Shown in the popup. Never transmitted |
| Pro license key + activation ID | `chrome.storage.local` | So Pro features work offline |

Uninstalling the extension deletes all of it.

**Pro license (optional):**
Pro features are unlocked via a one-time payment processed by [Polar](https://polar.sh), which acts as the Merchant of Record. Card processing is handled by Stripe. This extension **never sees your card details**.

* You purchase a license on Polar's checkout page. A license key is sent to your email.
* You paste the key into the extension to activate it. Each key allows up to 2 device activations.
* The extension calls `api.polar.sh` to activate and validate the key. The only data sent is the key itself and an opaque activation ID.
* The paid status is cached locally. The key is re-validated once per day.

The license check is the **only network call** this extension ever makes, and only if you purchase Pro.

**Permissions explained:**

| Permission | What it's for |
|------------|---------------|
| `contextMenus` | Adds the right-click menu |
| `downloads` | Saves the converted file to Downloads |
| `activeTab` | Temporary access to the current tab for image handling |
| `storage` | Remembers settings locally |
| `offscreen` | Provides a canvas to convert images (service workers have no DOM) |
| `notifications` | Tells you why a conversion failed |
| `scripting` | One-shot script for `blob:` image URLs in single-page apps |
| `<all_urls>` | Reads the bytes of whichever image you right-clicked, on any site |
| `clipboardRead` (optional) | Only requested when you press "Save image from clipboard" |

